data.name: MC_MailSettingsHelp
data.value:
The following macro’s are available:

{angleid}

Inserts the ID of the exported Angle.

{anglename}

Inserts the name of the exported Angle.

{anglename:normalized}

Inserts the normalized name of the exported Angle. When applied, all spaces and special characters used in the Angle name will be removed. A normalized name can for instance be used as file name.

{condition}

Condition for condition based automation task.

{conditionresult}

Condition result for condition based automation task.

{displayid}

Inserts the ID of the exported Display.

{displayname}

Inserts the name of the exported Display.

{displayname:normalized}

Inserts the normalized name of the exported Display. When applied, all spaces and special characters used in the Display name will be removed. A normalized name can for instance be used as file name.

{language}

Language of the exported data.

{model}

Inserts the ID of the model the Angle is part of.

{modeltimestamp}

Inserts the timestamp of the model the exported Angle is part of. {objectcount} Inserts the number of objects the Display contains.

{objectcount}

Amount of objects in the export.

{result}

Inserts the contents of the exported Display.

{rowsexported}

Inserts the number of rows exported for this Angle.

{rowstotal}

Inserts the number of rows available in the Display.

data.name: MC_AuthenticationProvidersHelpContainer
data.value:

In case you want to have the users retrieved from a different container, enter the Distinguished Name (DN) of this container here.
An Active Directory browsing tool can help you find the correct DN syntax for the container. For example, LDAP Admin is a free Windows LDAP client that lets you browse the Active Directory and copy the DN. Example DN: CN=External Users, DC=Contoso, DC=com

data.name: MC_ExportPackageURlDescription
data.value:
Make a selection of the desired Angles, Templates, Dashboards using the filter options in the search page of the Webclient. Copy and paste the URL here to create a package containing the same selection of items.
Multi-model selections are not supported. In case of multiple models, please make sure to select only one model in the General filters.
Note: Invalid Angles are not included in the package. If the results in the package don't match the results in the Web client, please check for invalid Angles.
